@subsection RS232 settings

X64 and X128 can support RS232 in the following ways:

@itemize @bullet
@item
by emulating Daniel Dallmann's 9600 baud userport-based RS232 interface;
@item
by emulating a 6551-based RS232 interface located at $DE00.
@end itemize

Each of these emulated devices can be either:

@itemize @bullet
@item
connected a real UNIX serial device;
@item
dumped to a file;
@item
piped through a process.
@end itemize

It is possible to define up to two UNIX serial devices, and then decide
which interface should be connected to which device.  Devices are
defined through the following settings:

@itemize @bullet
@item
``Serial 1 device@dots{}'' and ``Serial 2 device@dots{}'' are used to specify
the the pathnames of the serial devices, with the file selector;
@item
``Serial 1 baudrate'' and ``Serial 2 baudrate'' specify the baudrate.
@end itemize


