@node Snapshot usage, Snapshot format, Snapshots, Snapshots
@section Snapshot usage

A snapshot is one file. It contains the complete emulator state.
A snapshot file can be generated by selecting the @code{save snapshot}
menu entry at any time.

A snapshot file can be used to restore the emulator state by selecting
the @code{load snapshot} menu entry at any time.

@b{Warning}: The complete state is saved, but not restored are: 
@itemize @bullet
@item The ROMs. This can pose problems when restoring the state of a
PET 3032 into a PET 4032 for example. Also attached cartridges are
not saved. I.e. you have to attach them before restoring a snapshot
of run of such a cartridge.

@item The memory configuration. The VIC20, PET and CBM-II emulators
do have some memory expansion info. This is saved but not (yet??)
restored.

@end itemize

